text: CET Pitești is a high-rise abandoned chimney just outside of the city of Pitești, Romania. It was built as part of a planned coal-fired power plant, but the plant was never finished, leaving the chimney unused. The structure stands at 918.64 ft. ==See also== *List of tallest structures in Romania ==References== Category:Chimneys in Romania Category:Buildings and structures in Argeș County
title: CET Pitești
